			"type": "references",
			"content": "<h2 class=\"referenceHeader\" id=\"Referenser\">Referenser</h2>\n<ol class=\"references\"><li id=\"reference_1\"><a href=\"http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/amnesomraden/statistik-och-undersokningar/sjukdomsstatistik/tuberkulos/\">http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/amnesomraden/statistik-och-undersokningar/sjukdomsstatistik/tuberkulos</a></li>\n<li id=\"reference_2\"><a href=\"http://www.who.int/tb/publications/global_report/en/\">http://www.who.int/tb/publications/global_report/en/</a></li>\n<li id=\"reference_3\">Bruchfeld J, Correia-Neves M, K&auml;llenius G. Tuberculosis and HIV co-infection.<a href=\"http://www-ncbi-nlm-nih-gov.proxy.kib.ki.se/pubmed/25722472\"> </a><a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25722472\"><span>Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med</span>. 2015 Feb 26. pii: a017871</a>.</li>\n<li id=\"reference_4\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Askling et al</span></li>\n<li id=\"reference_5\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Arkema et a</span>l</li>\n<li id=\"reference_6\">Riley RL. 1974. Airborne infection. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/4212915\">Am J Med 57: 466&ndash;475</a>.</li>\n<li id=\"reference_7\">Nardell EA. Transmission and Institutional Infection Control of Tuberculosis. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26292985\"><span>Cold Spring Harb Perspect Med</span>. 2015 Aug 20;6(2). pii: a018192</a>.</li>\n<li id=\"reference_8\">Erkens CGM., Kamphorst M., Abubakar I. et al. Tuberculosis contact investigation in low prevalence countries: a European consensus. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20889463\">Eur Respir J.<span>&nbsp;</span>2010 Oct;36(4):925-49</a>.</li>\n<li id=\"reference_9\"><a href=\"http://www.who.int/tb/publications/latent-tuberculosis-infection/en/\">http://www.who.int/tb/publications/latent-tuberculosis-infection/en/</a></li>\n<li id=\"reference_10\">Loddenkemper R, Lipman M, Zumla A. Clinical aspects of adult Tuberculosis. <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/256593